[src:rbac-access-control/identity-and-access-management] Identity management (IdM) is the task of controlling information about users on computers.
[src:rbac-access-control/identity-and-access-management] Such information includes information that authenticates the identity of a user, and information that describes data and actions they are authorized to access and/or perform.
[src:rbac-access-control/identity-and-access-management] It also includes the management of descriptive information about the user and how and by whom that information can be accessed and modified.
[src:rbac-access-control/identity-and-access-management] In addition to users, managed entities typically include hardware and network resources and even applications.
